                        "name": "3.D.2 Graduates of health field of education",
                      
                        "goal": "Goal 3. Good health and well-being",
                      
                        "priority": "High level of education and professional training of medical staff and their availability to patients",
                      
                        "definition": "Number of medical graduates from public and private universities.",
                      
                        "unit": "persons",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "A graduate is a person who has completed the highest programmatic class in a given type of school and received a certificate of completion of this school - applies to graduates in schools covered by the education system. A graduate of studies receives a diploma of completion of studies in a specific field and profile confirming higher education and a professional title: 1. Bachelor's degree, engineer's degree or equivalent confirming higher education at the same level - in the case of first-cycle studies; 2. Master's degree, master of engineering or equivalent confirming higher education at the same level - in the case of second-cycle studies and uniform master's studies. A field of study is a separate part of one or several areas of education, implemented at the university in a manner specified by the education program. A public university is a university established by the state represented by the appropriate authority or public administration body.",
                      
                        "source": "Statistics Poland",
                      
                        "availability": "Annual data, since 2014",
                      
